    "uen": "198500717G",
    "description": "<p>Econflo Systems was founded as a traditional family business with big ideas. Way before caring for the environment and sustainability became trendy, our founder’s fundamental driver was the recognition that water-scarce Singapore was literally flushing its precious resource down the toilet.<br>\n<br>\nDriven by their professional experience in construction and engineering, Econflo Systems thought big and was the first to test and get approval for the technologically-advanced water-saving WC from Gustavsberg Sweden for use in Singapore. This reduced water used per flush from up to 11 litres back then to as low as 3 litres, with further improvement to 2.5 litres today.<br>\n<br>\nWith the widespread adoption of this technology, Econflo Systems had a hand in setting Singapore on the path to saving an immeasurable amount of water from this initial implementation. A rough estimate suggests that Singapore saves about 144 million litres of water a day with water-saving WCs of at least 2 WELS ticks compared to traditional WCs.</p>",
